We recommended the following:

Immediately correct the present system in handling PCF and ensure compliance with the NGAS for LGUs in maintaining the same under the imprest system;

Use the PCF only for those activities requiring items of small value equal to threshold when it is inconvenient to pay through check.

We recommended the following:
1. Create an inventory committee to conduct physical count of PPE. To ensure the success of the committee, all department heads are advised to instruct their members to cooperate in the conduct of physical count;

2. The inventory committee shall prepare the Physical Inventory Reports to be submitted to the Property Officer for verification and reconciliation with PPE Ledger Cards and the Property Cards to be maintained by the Accounting and Property Offices, respectively;

3. All fully depreciated PPE, if found unserviceable shall be classified to Other Assets; and

4. Proper disposal of unserviceable property should be made.

We recommended the following:

1. 	Direct the Municipal Treasurer to develop or adapt available databases for the proper updating, monitoring and determining the total delinquent RPT per taxpayer;
2. 	Direct the Municipal Treasurer to exert more effort to expedite the collection of taxes due and collectible by sending demand letters to delinquent taxpayers giving priority to delinquent taxpayers having large balances; 
3. 	Create a committee which is responsible in the conduct of an information dissemination drive regarding the importance of paying taxes promptly and the consequences of non-payment thereof; and
4. 	Avail of the remedies provided for by law to enforce the strict and prompt collection of delinquent real property taxes.
